rComments: Kai is a great instructor. I've spent most of my time at oft trying to get into Fantasy and Horror and my only complaints are with how the school chooses to  run the course:only one section offered, too short, etc. Kai is fun, well-spoken, and very good with creative assignments. 1010 would take again and again

Kai was a great instructor. I took this course this past spring term and I am not at all sure about what the post below is referring to ... It is a challenging course, but very doable. Prof. Hainer is approachable and encourages talking to her about assignments. I wish I had taken advantage of office hours - very possible to get an A in her class.

Although she could have been more encouraging to students' ideas during discussion, if you do your work and make an effort to participate in class you will find that this will be one of the most rewarding courses you ever take! She's an amazing close reader and she's so well-spoken. She's also a fair (maybe even generous) marker. Great prof!

One of the most articulate and insightful professors I've ever had. She is always prepared so her lectures are always amazing. She's also an extremely fair marker. Take her classes. She will blow you away with how smart she is!

She is by far one of the best profs I ever had! I got a 90 in her class. If you work hard & ask her for help, she will go out of her way to ensure you do great on assignments. What you put is what you get--if you work hard, you get great marks. If you don't, then you don't. Simple as that.

She's the worst prof I've ever had so far. It's her way or the highway as she doesn't appreciate opinions that differ from hers. And she's not afraid to humiliate you in front of the entire class. The best part is that her readings are demanding and excessive. Just because one knows the material, it necessarily doesn't mean that you're a good prof.
